President Samia Suluhu Hassan has made a minor reshuffle by exchanging Permanent Secretaries for the Ministry of Tourism and Natural Resources and Ministry of Education, Science and Technology. A press statement issued by the Directorate of Presidential Communication Thursday evening, Permanent Secretary in the Ministry of Tourism and Natural Resources, Dr Francis Michael has been moved to the Ministry of Education, Science and Technology. The Permanent Secretary in the Ministry of Education, Science and Technology, Prof Eliamani Sedoyeka has been shifted to the Ministry of Tourism and Natural Resources to cover the vacuum left by Dr Michael. The date for the appointees to take oaths of their respective offices will be announced later.